    • process

      public boolean process(Set<? extends TypeElement> annotations, RoundEnvironment roundEnv)
      During compilation checks whether each use of any design pattern is complete and correct. Called by the compiler in time of the annotation processing. Run dedicated Processor and its method process for every pattern and receives their processed annotations. Updates the file 'foundAnnotations.txt' with annotations found by those subprocessors, to make it ready for the next turn of incremental project building.
      Specified by:
      process in interface Processor
      Parameters:
      roundEnv - environment used during the round of processing annotations.
